[\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Yulo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo advanced to the all-around, floor exercise, and vault finals following the conclusion of the men's artistic gymnastics qualification at the Bercy Arena on Saturday, July 27 (Sunday, July 28, Manila time).\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 653, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 640, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"score\": 0.9901956685904264, \"rank\": 0.00989889523375374, \"text\": \"Manila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having learned his lessons from a disappointing campaign in the previous Tokyo Games, the 24-year-old star fueled medal hopes as he placed second in floor exercise and sixth in vault - events where he won world titles.\", \"from\": 655, \"to\": 873, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Yulo also did fairly well in the four other apparatuses, totaling 83.631 points to reach the all-around finals at ninth place.\", \"from\": 875, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top 24 in the all-around and the top eight in each apparatus advanced to the finals.\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1091, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bearing the responsibility of winning the Philippines' first Olympic gymnastics medal, Yulo showed he has what it takes as he shone in his pet events, recording 14.766 points in floor exercise and averaging 14.683 points in vault.\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1135, \"end\": 1146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.6678934824456046, \"rank\": 0.49721000107928814, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Only Great Britain's Jake Jarman netted a higher score than Yulo in the floor exercise qualification with 14.966 points, while defending champion Artem Dolgopyat of Israel landed at seventh with 14.466 points.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1343, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.6049836084086225, \"rank\": 0.6478056636216873, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1350, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"score\": 0.9937816377359641, \"rank\": 0.0034186218768425206, \"text\": \"Jake\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jake_Paul\"}, {\"begin\": 1490, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 0.9324185041444905, \"rank\": 0.07247958624116037, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In vault, Yulo garnered 14.800 and 14.566 points in his two attempts for an average of 14.683 points as he advanced to the final of the same apparatus for the second straight Olympics.\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1720, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ukraine's Nazar Chepurnyi topped the vault qualification with 14.833 points followed by Great Britain's Harry Hepworth (14.766), Croatia's Aurel Benovic (14.733), Ukraine's Igor Radivilov (14.700), and Jarman (14.699).\", \"from\": 1722, \"to\": 1940, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ukraine\", \"score\": 0.9999790061079281, \"rank\": 2.0994308197203248e-05, \"text\": \"Ukraine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"